outputs.description: Output 2: Capicity of MOET is enhanced to coordinate, plan, implement, and monitor provision of quality basic education withspecial attention for children with disabilities
Improved national capacity to coordinate, track and provide HIV services for adolescents in all districts, particularlyadolescent girls by 2018.
Targeted communities in all districts have knowledge and skills to exercise healthy sanitation and hygiene practices  by 2018.
5.4:  The MOSD, at all levels, leads, manages and implements a comprehensive and integrated social protection system.
A single national registry is institutionalized for use in management and monitoring of social assistance
